    "details": {
      "biography": {
        "value": "<h2>Vesten Quill — The Courier Handler</h2>\n<p><em>The handler above Trell, the courier in the dead-drop chain. Late thirties, lean, sharp-faced, soft-spoken. Operates from a rented room above a printer's shop on Quill Street under the cover identity of a quiet northern lawyer. Receives packets from Trell via the Hall of Bonds dead-drop; forwards them by his own channel to a Hardby-aligned letter agency operating out of a Greyhawk City address. Does not know the conspiracy's larger structure; treats the work as paid intermediary services. Will surrender at half HP. Will name the next layer up. Will not name the layer above that (he does not know).</em></p>\n<h3>Combat behavior</h3>\n<p><strong>Surrenders at half HP.</strong> Carries a scimitar, a hand crossbow, and a concealed dagger. Has a whistle on a cord around his neck — uses it on round 1 to summon one Thug from a neighboring rooftop (arrives round 3). Parry reaction makes him hard to hit on the first round of any engagement.</p>\n<h3>Statblock summary (CR 2, PB +2 — Bandit Captain analog)</h3>\n<p>AC 15 (studded leather) · HP 65 (10d8+20) · Speed 30 ft. · Init +3 · Passive Perception 10</p>\n<p>STR 15 · DEX 16 · CON 14 · INT 14 · WIS 11 · CHA 14. Saves: STR +4, DEX +5, WIS +2.</p>\n<p>Skills: Athletics +4, Deception +4. Senses: Passive Perception 10. Languages: Common, Old Aerdi, Hardby trade cipher.</p>\n<h3>Actions</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Multiattack.</strong> Two melee attacks (scimitar + dagger, or two scimitar) and one Hand Crossbow.</li>\n<li><strong>Scimitar.</strong> +5 melee, 1d6+3 slashing.</li>\n<li><strong>Dagger.</strong> +5 melee or thrown 20/60, 1d4+3 piercing.</li>\n<li><strong>Hand Crossbow.</strong> +5 ranged, range 30/120, 1d6+3 piercing.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Reactions</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Parry.</strong> When hit by a melee attack he can see, +2 to AC against that attack.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Optional support</h3>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Thug 1</strong> in the room with Quill (only if Quill has been warned). CR 1/2 SRD Thug. AC 11, HP 32, mace + heavy crossbow.</li>\n<li><strong>Thug 2</strong> arrives from a neighboring rooftop on round 3. Identical to Thug 1.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Source</h3>\n<p><em>Blooming Rot, Part 2 — Phase 5.</em> See <em>The Courier Chain — Tracing Up From Pell</em> in the Leak Operation journal for the encounter setup. <strong>This is the only combat encounter in Phase 5.</strong></p>",
        "public": ""
      },
